Auithors" description of sample preparation was as follows: {{i}}To prepare protein extracts, cells were re-suspended in an equal volume of lysis buffer (50mM Tris pH 8.0, 50mM NaCl, 1mM EDTA and 1 tablet of Complete Proteinase Inhibitor (Roche)/10ml) and incubated on ice for 30 minutes. Cells were then lysed with a dounce homogenizer and the soluble protein extracts obtained after centrifugation. For better lysis, 0.05% NP40 was added as a detergent. Prior to trypsin digest, detergent was removed using the Orgosol Detergent-Out kit. {{/i}}

From Abstract: {{i}}In this study, we combined three endoproteases (trypsin, Glu-C and Lys-C) with HPLC-MS/MS analysis and two types of peptide fragmentations, CID (collision induced dissociation) and HCD (higher-energy C-trap dissociation), to identify PIP isoforms and PTMs from broccoli roots. {{/i}}

column12: Data downloaded from [[http://www.marcottelab.org/MSdata/Data_11/ authors" website]], data file Sus2_b.RAW. Auithors" description of sample preparation was as follows: {{i}}To prepare protein extracts, cells were re-suspended in an equal volume of lysis buffer (50mM Tris pH 8.0, 50mM NaCl, 1mM EDTA and 1 tablet of Complete Proteinase Inhibitor (Roche)/10ml) and incubated on ice for 30 minutes. Cells were then lysed with a dounce homogenizer and the soluble protein extracts obtained after centrifugation. For better lysis, 0.05% NP40 was added as a detergent. Prior to trypsin digest, detergent was removed using the Orgosol Detergent-Out kit. {{/i}}

column1: Proteomic analysis of shoot tissue during photoperiod induced growth cessation in V. riparia Michx. grapevines
column12: PRIDE ID: 16374. Data published in Proteome Sci. 2010 Aug 12;8:44 ([[http://www.ncbi.nih.gov/pubmed/20704748 PubMed]]). From PRIDE: {{i}}To begin understanding transduction of the photoperiod signal, Vitis riparia Michx. (PI588259) grapevines that had grownfor 35 days in long photoperiod (long day, LD, 15h) were subjected to either continued LD or a short photoperiod (short day, SD, 13h) treatment. Shoot tips (4-node shoot terminals) were collected from each treatment at 7 and 28 days of LD and SD for proteomic analysis via two-dimensional (2D) gel electrophoresis. The peptides were identified using MALDI-TOF_TOF mass spectrometer after trypsin digestion. A master gel was made and mapped with all p roteins from both photoperiod treatments. The proteins were identified by matching thepeptide sequences against the 12X Vitis vinifera grape genome in NCBI. This study was funded in part by NSF grant DBI064755 and the South Dakota Agriculture Experiment Station.{{/i}}

column1: Proteomic analysis of shoot tissue during photoperiod induced growth cessation in V. riparia Michx. grapevines
column12: PRIDE ID: 16374. Data published in Proteome Sci. 2010 Aug 12;8:44 ([[http://www.ncbi.nih.gov/pubmed/20704748 PubMed]]). From PRIDE: {{i}}To begin understanding transduction of the photoperiod signal, Vitis riparia Michx. (PI588259) grapevines that had grownfor 35 days in long photoperiod (long day, LD, 15h) were subjected to either continued LD or a short photoperiod (short day, SD, 13h) treatment. Shoot tips (4-node shoot terminals) were collected from each treatment at 7 and 28 days of LD and SD for proteomic analysis via two-dimensional (2D) gel electrophoresis. The peptides were identified using MALDI-TOF_TOF mass spectrometer after trypsin digestion. A master gel was made and mapped with all p roteins from both photoperiod treatments. The proteins were identified by matching thepeptide sequences against the 12X Vitis vinifera grape genome in NCBI. This study was funded in part by NSF grant DBI064755 and the South Dakota Agriculture Experiment Station.{{/i}}

column1: Analysis of root plasma membrane aquaporins from Brassica oleracea: post-translational modifications, de novo sequencing and detection of isoforms by high resolution mass spectrometry.
column10: Plataforma de Prote-mica, CIC bioGUNE, CIBERehd, ProteoRed
column12: PRIDE ID: 9743. Trypsin digest. Published in J Proteome Res. 2010 Jul 2;9(7):3479-94 ([[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20462273 PubMed]]). From Abstract: {{i}}In this study, we combined three endoproteases (trypsin, Glu-C and Lys-C) with HPLC-MS/MS analysis and two types of peptide fragmentations, CID (collision induced dissociation) and HCD (higher-energy C-trap dissociation), to identify PIP isoforms and PTMs from broccoli roots. {{/i}}

column1: Data_11 - Rice (Oryza sativa) - Orbitrap - leaves, cell lysate
column12: Data downloaded from [[http://www.marcottelab.org/MSdata/Data_11/ authors" website]], data file Sus1_b.RAW. Auithors" description of sample preparation was as follows: {{i}}To prepare protein extracts, cells were re-suspended in an equal volume of lysis buffer (50mM Tris pH 8.0, 50mM NaCl, 1mM EDTA and 1 tablet of Complete Proteinase Inhibitor (Roche)/10ml) and incubated on ice for 30 minutes. Cells were then lysed with a dounce homogenizer and the soluble protein extracts obtained after centrifugation. For better lysis, 0.05% NP40 was added as a detergent. Prior to trypsin digest, detergent was removed using the Orgosol Detergent-Out kit. {{/i}}

Auithors" description of sample preparation was as follows: {{i}}To prepare protein extracts, cells were re-suspended in an equal volume of lysis buffer (50mM Tris pH 8.0, 50mM NaCl, 1mM EDTA and 1 tablet of Complete Proteinase Inhibitor (Roche)/10ml) and incubated on ice for 30 minutes. Cells were then lysed with a dounce homogenizer and the soluble protein extracts obtained after centrifugation. For better lysis, 0.05% NP40 was added as a detergent. Prior to trypsin digest, detergent was removed using the Orgosol Detergent-Out kit. {{/i}}

column12: Data downloaded from [[http://www.marcottelab.org/MSdata/Data_11/ authors" website]], data file Sus2_b.RAW. Auithors" description of sample preparation was as follows: {{i}}To prepare protein extracts, cells were re-suspended in an equal volume of lysis buffer (50mM Tris pH 8.0, 50mM NaCl, 1mM EDTA and 1 tablet of Complete Proteinase Inhibitor (Roche)/10ml) and incubated on ice for 30 minutes. Cells were then lysed with a dounce homogenizer and the soluble protein extracts obtained after centrifugation. For better lysis, 0.05% NP40 was added as a detergent. Prior to trypsin digest, detergent was removed using the Orgosol Detergent-Out kit. {{/i}}
